<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">MARKIT RISES ON DEBUT <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Shares of Markit, the big financial data provider, opened on Thursday above their initial public offering price, as investors proved eager for a piece of the newly public company, <b><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/06/19/shares-of-markit-rise-in-market-debut/">DealBookâs Michael J. de la Merced writes</a></b>. Markitâs stock opened at $26.15, about 9 percent above the I.P.O. price. The shares closed on Thursday at $26.70, up 11.3 percent on the day. Markit was the <b>biggest of eight companies to price I.P.O.s this week</b>, one of the busiest in recent months.</p>
